instance security_and_safety_considerations : DTDFVocab:SecuritySafety [
    base:desc "Security follows the hierarchy of the RAMI 4.0 reference architecture (Frysak et al. 48, D.D.I. 49).  All device communications are performed over MQTT using Mosquitto, which provides role‑based authentication, TLS 1.3 encryption, and broker‑side ACLs that enforce device identity and permission checks.  Thingsboard (53) supplements this with JWT‑based authentication, OAuth2 support, role‑based access control, and audit logging of every data transaction.  Safety‑critical operations are protected by fail‑safe mechanisms defined in the RAMI 4.0 Safety layer: high‑priority CAN messages deliver emergency stop commands, watchdog timers reset the control daemon on failure, and redundant control firmware implements ISO IEC 61508‑A9 safety integrity level requirements.  The model‑driven engineering method (Heithoff et al. 43) generates simulation models that are validated against IEC 61508 and IEC 61511 safety cases to certify the twin’s control logic before deployment."
